CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 21, 1945, pg. 26 reads: "Nuptials - Charming gathering at the wedding of the former Florence Williams and W. James Adams. The ceremony was performed at the home of the bride's parents, Mr. and Mrs. J. V. Williams, 2429 Waring Court, Terrace Village II.  Left to right :Jack Cooper, the groom, W. James Adams; the bride, Florence Williams; maid of honor, Mrs. Lou Williams; J. V. Williams, brother of the bride. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom W. James Adams and bride Florence Williams Adams wearing light colored suit with single square button and corsage, posed in front of curtain in home of J. V. Williams, 2429 Waring Court, Terrace Village II
